[normal]K[bold]ey and hidden assumptions.[bold]E
[normal]mbedded within the a
[normal]na
[normal]ly
[normal]s
[normal]is 
[normal]are two key assumptions, namely
[normal]:
[normal](1)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]GDP drives growth in demand
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]This assumption is difficult to sustain when it is realised that GDP grew, in real terms, by 160% between the 1955 and 1995 but that 
[normal]rail use grew not at all.  The implication is that the extraordinary growth since1995 is due to the razzamatazz of privatisation, aided by vast subsidies from the public purse; nothing at all to do with GDP and not likely to be sustained..
[normal](2)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
